Sentencas: Layered perovskites can be considered as promising cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cell because of their fast oxygen kinetics compared to simple perovskites.
Titulo: Investigation of the Fe doping effect on the B-site of the layered perovskite PrBa0.8Ca0.2Co2O5+δ for a promising cathode material of the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Among them, the cobalt-based layered perovskites are considered as very promising cathode materials due to its high conductivity and fast oxygen kinetics, but they are unstable under operating condition.
Titulo: Investigation of the Fe doping effect on the B-site of the layered perovskite PrBa0.8Ca0.2Co2O5+δ for a promising cathode material of the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Doping other transition metal such as Fe, Mn, Cu, and Ni can be considered to solve the instability of the cobalt-based layered perovskites.
Titulo: Investigation of the Fe doping effect on the B-site of the layered perovskite PrBa0.8Ca0.2Co2O5+δ for a promising cathode material of the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this paper, we investigated Fe doped cobalt-based layered perovskite, PrBa0.8Ca0.2CO2-xFexO5+delta (x = 0, 0.5, and 1.0), as prospective cathode materials in terms of their crystal structures, thermal expansion behavior, electro- and electro-chemical properties.
Titulo: Investigation of the Fe doping effect on the B-site of the layered perovskite PrBa0.8Ca0.2Co2O5+δ for a promising cathode material of the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The PrBa0.8Ca0.2Co1.5Fe0.5O5+delta shows improved maximum power density of 1.89 W cm(-2) and polarization resistance of 0.080 Omega cm(2) at 600 degrees C as compared with un-doped PrBa0.8Ca0.2CO2O5+delta while maintaining suppressed thermal expansion.
Titulo: Investigation of the Fe doping effect on the B-site of the layered perovskite PrBa0.8Ca0.2Co2O5+δ for a promising cathode material of the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Based on these results, PrBa0.8Ca0.2CO1.5Fe0.5O5+delta can be considered as a promising cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Investigation of the Fe doping effect on the B-site of the layered perovskite PrBa0.8Ca0.2Co2O5+δ for a promising cathode material of the intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
